20 payment to each county the sum of the amounts computed by multiplying the credit
21 allowed for each homestead of a disabled veteran in the county by the total of the tax
22 mill rates, exclusive of any state mill rates that were applied to other real estate in the
23 taxing districts for the preceding year.
24 10. The county treasurer upon receipt of the payment from the state treasurer shall
25 apportion and distribute the payment without delay to the county and to the local
26 taxing districts of the county on the basis on which the general real estate tax for the
27 preceding year is apportioned and distributed.
